rdf:Description.rdfs:label: analyzed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through analysis of artifacts (e.g., executables, packages, containers, and virtual machine images) after its build. Such analysis generally requires a variety of heuristics. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as a "3rd party" SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityAdversaryModel
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the security adversary model for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: red
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Data points in the dataset are highly confidential and can only be shared with named recipients.
A collection of SPDX Elements describing a single package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: buildSystem
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference build system used to create or publish the package.
A canonical, unique, immutable identifier
Provides a NamespaceMap of prefixes and associated namespace partial URIs applicable to an SpdxDocument and independent of any specific serialization format or instance.
A mathematically calculated representation of a grouping of data.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element doesn't fit into any of the other categories

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cwe
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Weakness Enumeration](https://csrc.nist.gov/glossary/term/common_weakness_enumeration). A reference to a source of software flaw defined within the official [CWE List](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/) that conforms to the [CWE specification](https://cwe.mitre.org/).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: support
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the software support channel or other support information for a package.
A probability score between 0 and 1 of a vulnerability being exploited.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: design
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM of intended, planned software project or product with included components (some of which may not yet exist) for a new software artifact.
Specifies the CVSS base, temporal, threat, or environmental severity type.
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this ListedLicense or ListedLicenseException identifier was first added.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Makes no assertion about the field.
Indicates the type of support that is associated with an artifact.
Refers to any unit of content that can be associated with a distribution of software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: altWebPage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an alternative web page.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: categorical
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data that is classified into a discrete number of categories, such as the eye color of a population of people.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Concise Software Identification (CoSWID) tag, as defined in [RFC 9393](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc9393) Section 2.3.
Specifies the CVSS vector string for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: reportedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Designates a `from` Vulnerability was first reported to a project, vendor, or tracking database for formal identification by each `to` Agent.
Specifies the exploit catalog type.
Provides an exploit assessment of a vulnerability.
A reference to a resource identifier defined outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content that uniquely identifies an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityAdvisory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a published security advisory (where advisory as defined per [ISO 29147:2018](https://www.iso.org/standard/72311.html)) that may affect one or more elements, e.g., vendor advisories or specific NVD entries.
This property is used to denote the root Element(s) of a tree of elements contained in a BOM.
Connects a vulnerability and an element designating the element as a product affected by the vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake3
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [BLAKE3](https://github.com/BLAKE3-team/BLAKE3-specs/blob/master/blake3.pdf)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: foundBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Designates a `from` Vulnerability was originally discovered by the `to` Agent(s).
Provides the location of an external reference.
A mapping between prefixes and namespace partial URIs.
Specifies an Element contained in a piece of software where a vulnerability was found.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: security
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Security profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtimeAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a runtime analysis report for a package.
A license exception that is listed on the SPDX Exceptions list.
Provide context for a relationship that occurs in the lifecycle.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: bower
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Bower package. The package locator format, looks like `package#version`, is defined in the "install" section of [Bower API documentation](https://bower.io/docs/api/#install).
Provides a reference number that can be used to understand how to parse and interpret an Element.
Identifies who or what created the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: underInvestigationFor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Vulnerability impact is being investigated for each `to` Element. The use of the `underInvestigationFor` type is constrained to `VexUnderInvestigationVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Other exploit catalogs
The class that helps note down the quantity of energy consumption and the unit used for measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasExample
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is an example for the `from` Element (`from` hasExample `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: executable
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is an Artifact that can be run on a computer

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: riskAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a risk assessment for a package.
Provides a CVSS version 4 assessment for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The second-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: diskImage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a disk image that can be written to a disk, booted in a VM, etc. A disk image typically contains most or all of the components necessary to boot, such as bootloaders, kernels, firmware, userspace, etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: firmware
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element provides low level control over a device's hardware

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: no
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Indicates absence of the field.
Property describing a parameter used in an instance of a build.
A software agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: archive
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is an archived collection of one or more files (.tar, .zip, etc)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: simpleLicensing
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the simple Licensing profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md2
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: MD2 message-digest algorithm, as defined in [RFC 1319](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1319/).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is related to the `from` Element where the relationship type is not described by any of the SPDX relationhip types (this relationship is directionless).
A collection of Elements, not necessarily with unifying context.
Abstract ancestor class for all vulnerability assessments
A container for a grouping of SPDX-3.0 content characterizing details (provenence, composition, licensing, etc.) about a product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasOutputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build element generates each `to` Element as an output, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: amber
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Data points in the dataset can be shared only with specific organizations and their clients on a need to know basis.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDynamicLink
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element dynamically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Points to a resource outside the scope of the SPDX-3.0 content that provides additional characteristics of an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 256, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandedLicensing
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the expanded Licensing profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: affects
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Vulnerability affects each `to` Element. The use of the `affects` type is constrained to `VexAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.
Captures the size of the dataset.
Provides relevant information about the AI software, not including the model description.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: falcon
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [FALCON](https://falcon-sign.info/falcon.pdf)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: chat
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the instant messaging system used by the maintainer for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: image
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is a collection of images such as pictures of animals.
A collection of SPDX Elements that could potentially be serialized.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: attend
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerability requires attention from the organization's internal, supervisory-level individuals. Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, and may involve publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. CISA recommends remediating Attend vulnerabilities sooner than standard update timelines.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single or a collection of source files
Specifies until when the artifact can be used before its usage needs to be reassessed.
A type of extension consisting of a list of name value pairs.
Specifies the value of the content identifier.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: issueTracker
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the issue tracker for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseHistory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a published list of releases for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: npm
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an npm package. The package locator format is defined in the [npm documentation](https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/configuring-npm/package-json) and looks like `package@version`.
An Element an annotator has made an assertion about.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerabilityExploitabilityAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Vulnerability Exploitability eXchange (VEX) statement which provides information on whether a product is impacted by a specific vulnerability in an included package and, if affected, whether there are actions recommended to remediate. See also [NTIA VEX one-page summary](https://ntia.gov/files/ntia/publications/vex_one-page_summary.pdf).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: development
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during development phase of an element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: componentNotPresent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The software is not affected because the vulnerable component is not in the product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: kev
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: CISA's Known Exploited Vulnerability (KEV) Catalog
Provides a detailed description of the Element.
Specifies the type of the external reference.
Identifies the full text of a License or Addition.
A tuple of two positive integers that define a range.
A string in the license expression format.
An individual human being.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Gitoid](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid), stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects). A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: audio
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is audio based, such as a collection of music from the 80s.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasEvidence
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is considered as evidence for the `from` Element (`from` hasEvidence `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: modifiedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is modified by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandsTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` archive expands out as an artifact described by each `to` Element.
Specifies a data package and its associated information.
Indicates the amount of energy consumption incurred by an AI model.
A reference to a resource outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content related to an Element.
A name used in a CdxExtension name-value pair.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: descendantOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is a descendant of each `to` Element.
An SPDX version 2.X compatible verification method for software packages.
Capture the scope of information about a specific relationship between elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: platform
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element represents a runtime environment

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a version control system related to a software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is no support for the artifact from the supplier, consumer assumes any support obligations.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: none
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is 0.0
Artifact representing a serialization instance of SPDX data containing the definition of a particular Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: configures
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is a configuration applied to each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Refers to any object that stores content on a computer.
Specifies the exploit catalog type.
Specifies the unit in which energy is measured.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: track
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerability does not require action at this time. The organization would continue to track the vulnerability and reassess it if new information becomes available. CISA recommends remediating Track vulnerabilities within standard update timelines.
A distinct article or unit related to Software.
An Individual Value for License where the SPDX data creator determines that no license is present.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: availableFrom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is available from the additional supplier described by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cpe23
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Platform Enumeration: Naming Specification Version 2.3](https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/nistir/7695/final)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: patchedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a patch for the `from` Element (`from` patchedBy `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: publishedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Designates a `from` Vulnerability was made available for public use or reference by each `to` Agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated as part of the process of building the software to create a releasable artifact (e.g., executable or package) from data such as source files, dependencies, built components, build process ephemeral data, and other SBOMs.
A substitute for a URI.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a License which has additional text applied to it.
Provides the location of an exploit catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's build phase, during development.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: operatingSystem
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is an operating system

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exportControlAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a export control assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: syntactic
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data describes the syntax or semantics of a language or text, such as a parse tree used for natural language processing.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: purchaseOrder
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a purchase order for a package.
Links a vulnerability and elements representing products (in the VEX sense) where a fix has been applied and are no longer affected.
Specifies the version of a VEX statement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: megajoule
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Megajoule.
Defines the end of a range.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDataFile
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element treats each `to` Element as a data file. A data file is an artifact that stores data required or optional for the `from` Element's functionality. A data file can be a database file, an index file, a log file, an AI model file, a calibration data file, a temporary file, a backup file, and more. For AI training dataset, test dataset, test artifact, configuration data, build input data, and build output data, please consider using the more specific relationship types: `trainedOn`, `testedOn`, `hasTest`, `configures`, `hasInputs`, and `hasOutputs`, respectively. This relationship does not imply dependency.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through instrumenting the system running the software, to capture only components present in the system, as well as external call-outs or dynamically loaded components. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as an "Instrumented" or "Dynamic" SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Gitoid](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid), stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects). A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: No assertion can be made about the completeness of the relationship.
Contains a URL where the License or LicenseAddition can be found in use.
The relative file name of a file to be excluded from the `PackageVerificationCode`.
Provides information about the creation of the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: requirement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element provides a requirement needed as input for another Element
Abstract class for the portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a license.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: numeric
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists only of numeric entries.
Defines the beginning of a range.
Describes potentially noisy elements of the dataset.
Provides information about the creation of the Element.
Asbtract ancestor class for all VEX relationships

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: patch
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element contains a set of changes to update, fix, or improve another Element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDistributionArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is distributed as an artifact in each Element `to` (e.g. an RPM or archive file).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: device
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a chipset, processor, or electronic board
Identify the version of a package.
A short description of an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasStaticLink
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element statically links in each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasHost
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build was run on the `to` Element during a LifecycleScopeType period (e.g. the host that the build runs on).
Uniquely identifies an external element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: incomplete
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known not to be exhaustive.
Provides information about the primary purpose of the software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: act
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerability requires attention from the organization's internal, supervisory-level and leadership-level individuals. Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, as well as publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. Typically, internal groups would meet to determine the overall response and then execute agreed upon actions. CISA recommends remediating Act vulnerabilities as soon as possible.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: altDownloadLocation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an alternative download location.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: review
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when someone reviews the Element.
Links a vulnerability and one or more elements designating the latter as products not affected by the vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: specification
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a plan, guideline or strategy how to create, perform or analyse an application

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: usesTool
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element uses each `to` Element as a tool, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Describes if a given file is a directory or non-directory kind of file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: low
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Low/no risk is posed by an AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 384, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).
A map of Element identifiers that are used within a Document but defined external to that Document.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md5
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: MD5 message-digest algorithm, as defined in [RFC 1321](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1321).
Specifies the time from which an element is applicable / valid.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: data
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is data
Property that describes the URI of the build configuration source file.
Identifies an external Element used within a Document but defined external to that Document.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasProvidedDependency
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a dependency on each `to` Element, dependency is not in the distributed artifact, but assumed to be provided, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: test
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's testing phase, during development.
The version of the SPDX License List used in the license expression.
Enumeration of the valid profiles.
Specifies the CVSS qualitative severity rating of a vulnerability in relation to a piece of software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: delegatedTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Agent is delegating an action to the Agent of the `to` Relationship (which must be of type invokedBy), during a LifecycleScopeType (e.g. the `to` invokedBy Relationship is being done on behalf of `from`).
Describes the preprocessing steps that were applied to the raw data to create the given dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: any hashing algorithm that does not exist in this list of entries

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha1
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-1, a secure hashing algorithm, as defined in [RFC 3174](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3174).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sensor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded from a physical sensor, such as a thermometer reading or biometric device.
Abstract class representing a License or an OrLaterOperator.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_224
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 224, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).
Specifies an AI package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: secureSoftwareAttestation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to information assuring that the software is developed using security practices as defined by [NIST SP 800-218 Secure Software Development Framework (SSDF) Version 1.1](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/218/final) or [CISA Secure Software Development Attestation Form](https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/secure-software-development-attestation-form).
Specifies the time from which an element is no longer applicable / valid.
Provides information about the content type of an Element or a Property.
Describes what the given dataset should be used for.
A class for describing the energy consumption incurred by an AI model in different stages of its lifecycle.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 256, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).
Describes how the dataset was collected.
Specifies the time an artifact was released.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: configuration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is configuration data

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: timestamp
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded with a timestamp for each entry, but not necessarily ordered or at specific intervals, such as when a taxi ride starts and ends.
Specifies the SPDX License List version in which this license or exception identifier was deprecated.
Describes methods that can be used to explain the results from the AI model.
A canonical, unique, immutable identifier of the artifact content, that may be used for verifying its identity and/or integrity.
Provides an indication of where to retrieve an external Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deployed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: in addition to being supported by the supplier, the software is known to have been deployed and is in use. For a software as a service provider, this implies the software is now available as a service.
References an Element on the right-hand side of a relationship.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: qualityAssessmentReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a quality assessment for a package.
Provides a place for the SPDX data creator to record acknowledgement text for a software Package, File or Snippet.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: graph
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is in the form of a graph where entries are somehow related to each other through edges, such a social network of friends.
Availability of dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: privacyAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a privacy assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: System Package Data Exchange (SPDX) Ontology
rdf:Description.dcterms:abstract: This ontology defines the terms and relationships used in the SPDX specification to describe system packages
rdf:Description.dcterms:creator: SPDX Project
rdf:Description.dcterms:title: System Package Data Exchange (SPDX) Ontology

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityThreatModel
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference the [security threat model](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Threat_model) for a package.
Specifies whether the License is listed as approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDeletedFile
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a file deleted from the `from` Element (`from` hasDeletedFile `to`).
Records the time when a recommended action was communicated in a VEX statement to mitigate a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: application
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software application

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: eolNotice
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the End Of Sale (EOS) and/or End Of Life (EOL) information related to a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: documentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the documentation for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasPrerequisite
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a prerequisite on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 7.0 - 8.9
Enumeration of the different kinds of SPDX file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasOptionalDependency
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element optionally depends on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
The name of a relevant standard that may apply to an artifact.
Base domain class from which all other SPDX-3.0 domain classes derive.
Provides an ExternalMap of Element identifiers.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: extension
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Extension profile specification
Provides a CVSS version 3 assessment for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityPolicy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to instructions for reporting newly discovered security vulnerabilities for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasOptionalComponent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is an optional component of the `from` Element (`from` hasOptionalComponent `to`).
Abstract class representing a license combination consisting of one or more licenses.
Provides advise on how to mitigate or remediate a vulnerability when a VEX product is affected by it.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDeclaredLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact was discovered to actually contain each `to` license, for example as detected by use of automated tooling.
Describes the type of the given dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: serializedInArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` SPDXDocument can be found in a serialized form in each `to` Artifact.
Captures the threshold that was used for computation of a metric described in the metric field.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cpe22
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Platform Enumeration Specification 2.2](https://cpe.mitre.org/files/cpe-specification_2.2.pdf)
A buildId is a locally unique identifier used by a builder to identify a unique instance of a build produced by it.
References the Element on the left-hand side of a relationship.
Class that describes a build instance of software/artifacts.
Captures the domain in which the AI package can be used.
Commentary on an assertion that an annotator has made.
Specifies the time when a vulnerability was published.
An SPDX Element containing an SPDX license expression string.
Provides a numerical (0-10) representation of the severity of a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 512, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Build profile specification
A license that is not listed on the SPDX License List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: clear
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Dataset may be distributed freely, without restriction.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deviceDriver
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element represents software that controls hardware devices
Explains why a VEX product is not affected by a vulnerability. It is an alternative in VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship to the machine-readable justification label.
Provide consumers with comments by the creator of the Element about the Element.
Describes if any sensitive personal information is present in the dataset.
An Individual Value for License when no assertion can be made about its actual value.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: clickthrough
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is not publicly available and can only be accessed after affirmatively accepting terms on a clickthrough webpage.
Describes the type of annotation.
Provides a reference to a resource outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content that uniquely identifies an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metrics
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to metrics related to package such as OpenSSF scorecards.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasRequirement
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a requirement on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Provides additional purpose information of the software artifact.
An element of hardware and/or software utilized to carry out a particular function.
Defines the line range in the original host file that the snippet information applies to.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityPenTestReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a [penetration test](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penetration_test) report for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The third-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.
A place for the SPDX document creator to record a website that serves as the package's home page.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: limitedSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the artifact has been released, and there is limited support available from the supplier. There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information where only one of the elements applies.
Identifies from where or whom the Element originally came.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: test
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The Element is a test used to verify functionality on an software element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM created directly from the development environment, source files, and included dependencies used to build an product artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha224
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 224, as defined in [RFC 3874](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3874).
Specifies whether a license or additional text identifier has been marked as deprecated.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: kilowattHour
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Kilowatt-hour.
A license addition that is not listed on the SPDX Exceptions List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: module
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a module of a piece of software

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: green
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Dataset can be shared within a community of peers and partners.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dynamicAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a dynamic analysis report for a package.
A key used in a generic key-value pair.
Specifies whether an additional text identifier has been marked as deprecated.
Information about the relationship between two Elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: yes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Indicates presence of the field.
Abstract class for additional text intended to be added to a License, but which is not itself a standalone License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: complete
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known to be exhaustive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: software
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Software profile specification
A characterization of some aspect of an Element that is associated with the Element in a generalized fashion.
Provides a License author's preferred text to indicate that a file is covered by the License.
Indicates whether a relationship is known to be complete, incomplete, or if no assertion is made with respect to relationship completeness.
Provides an independently reproducible mechanism that permits verification of a specific Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: container
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a container image which can be used by a container runtime application

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when there is a security related identifier of unspecified type.
A collection of Elements that have a shared context.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: doesNotAffect
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Vulnerability has no impact on each `to` Element. The use of the `doesNotAffect` is constrained to `VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.
An entity that is authorized to issue identification credentials.
Provides a CVSS version 2.0 assessment for a vulnerability.
A value used in a generic key-value pair.
A distinct article or unit within the digital domain.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: manifest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software manifest
A license or addition that is not listed on the SPDX License List.
A license expression participating in a license set.
A LicenseAddition participating in a 'with addition' model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mavenCentral
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Maven repository artifact. The artifact locator format is defined in the [Maven documentation](https://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-naming-conventions.html) and looks like `groupId:artifactId[:version]`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: registration
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is not publicly available and an email registration is required before accessing the dataset, although without an affirmative acceptance of terms.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when the type does not match any of the other options.
Maps a LicenseRef or AdditionRef string for a Custom License or a Custom License Addition to its URI ID.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during the execution phase of an element.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information where all elements apply.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cve
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures identifiers, an identifier for a specific software flaw defined within the official CVE Dictionary and that conforms to the [CVE specification](https://csrc.nist.gov/glossary/term/cve_id).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: video
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is video based, such as a collection of movie clips featuring Tom Hanks.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: scrapingScript
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset provider is not making available the underlying data and the dataset must be reassembled, typically using the provided script for scraping the data.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to related security information of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: crystalsKyber
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Kyber](https://pq-crystals.org/kyber/)
Specifies whether the License is listed as free by the Free Software Foundation (FSF).
Specifies a time when a vulnerability assessment was modified
Describes a relationship between one or more elements.
Specifies an Extension characterization of some aspect of an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 384, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: republishedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Designates a `from` Vulnerability's details were tracked, aggregated, and/or enriched to improve context (i.e. NVD) by each `to` Agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: lite
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Lite profile specification
Property describing the session in which a build is invoked.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseNotes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the release notes for a package.
Describes a certain part of a file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Any other units of energy measurement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The file represents a directory and all content stored in that directory.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: socialMedia
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a social media channel for a package.
Provides an EPSS assessment for a vulnerability.
Describes a sensor used for collecting the data.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasSpecification
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a specification for the `from` Element (`from` hasSpecification `to`), during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Specifies a vulnerability and its associated information.
Specifies the level of support associated with an artifact.
Information about the relationship between two Elements.
Identifies the full text of a License, in SPDX templating format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasInputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build has each `to` Elements as an input, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: testedOn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has been tested on the `to` Element(s).

Provide the enumeration of possible decisions in the [Stakeholder-Specific Vulnerability Categorization (SSVC) decision tree](https://www.cisa.gov/stakeholder-specific-vulnerability-categorization-ssvc).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: copiedTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has been copied to each `to` Element.
Records the measurement of prediction quality of the AI model.
Records the type of the model used in the AI software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: describes
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element describes each `to` Element. To denote the root(s) of a tree of elements in a collection, the rootElement property should be used.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: filesystemImage
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a file system image that can be written to a disk (or virtual) partition
Specifies the type of the external identifier.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: coordinatedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Vulnerability is coordinatedBy the `to` Agent(s) (vendor, researcher, or consumer agent).
Represents the energy quantity.
Property that describes the time at which a build stops.
Specifies the SSVC decision type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exploitCreatedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Vulnerability has had an exploit created against it by each `to` Agent.
Provides the license under which the SPDX documentation of the Element can be used.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: crystalsDilithium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Dilithium](https://pq-crystals.org/dilithium/)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasVariant
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a variant the `from` Element (`from` hasVariant `to`).
Categories of confidentiality level.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is of a type not included in this list.
A buildType is a hint that is used to indicate the toolchain, platform, or infrastructure that the build was invoked on.
Identifies the tooling that was used during the creation of the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: nuget
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a NuGet package. The package locator format is defined in the [NuGet documentation](https://docs.nuget.org) and looks like `package/version`.
A property name with an associated value.
A License participating in a 'with addition' model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is metadata about the `from` Element (`from` hasMetadata `to`).
An Individual Value for Element representing a set of Elements of unknown identify or cardinality (number).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mailingList
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the mailing list used by the maintainer for a package.
Describes one a profile which the creator of this ElementCollection intends to conform to.
Designates elements as products where the impact of a vulnerability is being investigated.
Specified the time and date when a vulnerability was withdrawn.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: model
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a machine learning or artificial intelligence model

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md4
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: MD4 message-digest algorithm, as defined in [RFC 1186](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1186).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: no assertion about the type of support is made. This is considered the default if no other support type is used.
A key with an associated value.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dependsOn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element depends on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: fixedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Designates a `from` Vulnerability has been fixed by the `to` Agent(s).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: query
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is publicly available, but not all at once, and can only be accessed through queries which return parts of the dataset.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed when training the AI model that is being used in the AI system.
The percentile of the current probability score.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used to store extra information about an Element which is not part of a Review (e.g. extra information provided during the creation of the Element).
Gives information about the circumstances or unifying properties that Elements of the bundle have been assembled under.
The result of applying a hash algorithm to an Element.
An assertion made in relation to one or more elements.
Records the biases that the dataset is known to encompass.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: packagedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a packaged instance of the `from` Element (`from` packagedBy `to`).
Describes the confidentiality level of the data points contained in the dataset.
Categories of presence or absence.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: staticAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a static analysis report for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: adler32
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Adler-32 checksum is part of the widely used zlib compression library as defined in [RFC 1950](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc1950) Section 2.3.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: urlScheme
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) Schemes](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/uri-schemes.xhtml). The scheme used in order to locate a resource.
Conveys information about how VEX status was determined.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDocumentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is documented by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data type is not known.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityFix
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the patch or source code that fixes a vulnerability.
Specifies the licenseId that is preferred to be used in place of a deprecated License or LicenseAddition.
Identifies the download Uniform Resource Identifier for the package at the time that the document was created.
An Individual Value for Element representing a set of Elements with cardinality (number/count) of zero.
A license that is listed on the SPDX License List.
A mathematical algorithm that maps data of arbitrary size to a bit string.
Describes all the preprocessing steps applied to the training data before the model training.
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition, in SPDX templating format.
Describes relevant information about different steps of the training process.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerabilityDisclosureReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Vulnerability Disclosure Report (VDR) which provides the software supplier's analysis and findings describing the impact (or lack of impact) that reported vulnerabilities have on packages or products in the supplier's SBOM as defined in [NIST SP 800-161 Cybersecurity Supply Chain Risk Management Practices for Systems and Organizations](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/161/r1/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: low
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 0.1 - 3.9

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: license
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to additional license information related to an artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sourceArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an artifact containing the sources for a package.
Provides information about the completeness of relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: binaryArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to binary artifacts related to a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: file
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The file represents a single file (default).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: text
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists of unstructured text, such as a book, Wikipedia article (without images), or transcript.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: file
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single file which can be independently distributed (configuration file, statically linked binary, Kubernetes deployment, etc)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deployed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM provides an inventory of software that is present on a system. This may be an assembly of other SBOMs that combines analysis of configuration options, and examination of execution behavior in a (potentially simulated) deployment environment.
Provides an unambiguous mechanism for conveying a URI fragment portion of an Element ID.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ai
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the AI profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: contains
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element contains each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: development
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the artifact is in active development and is not considered ready for formal support from the supplier.
The field describes the availability of a dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md6
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [MD6 hash function](https://people.csail.mit.edu/rivest/pubs/RABCx08.pdf)
Property that describes the digest of the build configuration file used to invoke a build.
Captures a limitation of the AI software.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeCannotBeControlledByAdversary
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerable component is present, and the component contains the vulnerable code. However, vulnerable code is used in such a way that an attacker cannot mount any anticipated attack.
Records any relevant background information or additional comments about the origin of the package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: email
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Email address, as defined in [RFC 3696](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3986) Section 3.
Impact justification label to be used when linking a vulnerability to an element representing a VEX product with a VexNotAffectedVulnAssessmentRelationship relationship.
Defines the byte range in the original host file that the snippet information applies to.
Specifies the type of an annotation.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: structured
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is stored in tabular format or retrieved from a relational database.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when the type does not match any of the other options.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swhid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, a persistent intrinsic identifier for digital artifacts, such as files, trees (also known as directories or folders), commits, and other objects typically found in version control systems. The format of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) (ISO/IEC DIS 18670). They typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: documentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is documentation
Property describes the invocation entrypoint of a build.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasTest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a test artifact for the `from` Element (`from` hasTest `to`), during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: fixedIn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A `from` Vulnerability has been fixed in each of the `to` Element(s). The use of the `fixedIn` type is constrained to `VexFixedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.
Identifies all the text and metadata associated with a license in the license XML format.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed when finetuning the AI model that is being used in the AI system.
Captures a standard that is being complied with.
Records a hyperparameter used to build the AI model contained in the AI package.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed during inference time by an AI model that is being used in the AI system.
Defines the original host file that the snippet information applies to.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swhid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, a persistent intrinsic identifier for digital artifacts, such as files, trees (also known as directories or folders), commits, and other objects typically found in version control systems. The format of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) (ISO/IEC DIS 18670). They typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAssessmentFor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Relates a `from` Vulnerability and each `to` Element(s) with a security assessment. To be used with `VulnAssessmentRelationship` types.
Describes the anonymization methods used.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: packageUrl
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Package URL, as defined in the corresponding [Annex](../../../annexes/pkg-url-specification.md) of this specification.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeNotInExecutePath
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The affected code is not reachable through the execution of the code, including non-anticipated states of the product.
Provides the location for more information regarding an external identifier.
Specifies the type of an external identifier.
Specifies the unit of energy consumption.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: trackStar
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: ("Track\*" in the SSVC spec) The vulnerability contains specific characteristics that may require closer monitoring for changes. CISA recommends remediating Track\* vulnerabilities within standard update timelines.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 512, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 384, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasTestCase
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a test case for the `from` Element (`from` hasTestCase `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDependencyManifest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has manifest files that contain dependency information in each `to` Element.
A concrete subclass of AnyLicenseInfo used by Individuals in the ExpandedLicensing profile.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dataset
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Dataset profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: core
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Core profile specification
Property describing the start time of a build.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has other specific context information necessary to capture that the above set of enumerations does not handle.
Provides an SSVC assessment for a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: certificationReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a certification report for a package from an accredited/independent body.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: trainedOn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has been trained on the `to` Element(s).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Built-in inline controls or mitigations prevent an adversary from leveraging the vulnerability.
Agent represents anything with the potential to act on a system.
A group of people who work together in an organized way for a shared purpose.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: framework
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software framework

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: invokedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element was invoked by the `to` Agent, during a LifecycleScopeType period (for example, a Build element that describes a build step).
Refers to one or more Elements that are part of an ElementCollection.
Records the results of general safety risk assessment of the AI system.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directDownload
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is publicly available and can be downloaded directly.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 4.0 - 6.9

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: bom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is a bill of materials

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: componentAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Software Composition Analysis (SCA) report.
Specifies the VEX justification type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAddedFile
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a file added to the `from` Element (`from` hasAddedFile `to`).
Provides information about the type of an SBOM.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: critical
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 9.0 - 10.0

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: design
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's design.
Describe that a CVE is known to have an exploit because it's been listed in an exploit catalog.
Identifies when the Element was originally created.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: endOfSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is a defined end of support for the artifact from the supplier. This may also be referred to as end of life. There is a validUntilDate that can be used to signal when support ends for the artifact.
Specifies the type of the content identifier.
Identifies the text of one or more copyright notices for a software Package, File or Snippet, if any.
Provides a place for the SPDX data creator to record the package URL string (in accordance with the Package URL specification) for a software Package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: buildMeta
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference build metadata related to a published package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: amendedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is amended by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: productMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to additional product metadata such as reference within organization's product catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: support
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the artifact has been released, and is supported from the supplier. There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAssociatedVulnerability
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used to associate a `from` Artifact with each `to` Vulnerability.
Specifies the algorithm used for calculating the hash value.
Enumeration of dataset types.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: serious
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The highest level of risk posed by an AI system.
Indicates whether the system can perform a decision or action without human involvement or guidance.
Provides a set of values to be used to describe the common types of SBOMs that tools may create.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing this version, or any later version, of the indicated License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: install
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is used to install software on disk
Identifies who or what supplied the artifact or VulnAssessmentRelationship referenced by the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: library
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software library

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 512, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.
Provide an enumerated set of lifecycle phases that can provide context to relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: evidence
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is the evidence that a specification or requirement has been fulfilled

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: funding
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to funding information related to a package.
Specifies the type of a content identifier.
Identifies the name of an Element as designated by the creator.
Describes a mechanism to update the dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: generates
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element generates each `to` Element.
A License participating in an 'or later' model.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ancestorOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is an ancestor of each `to` Element.
Specifies the type of an external reference.
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition.
Provides information about the primary purpose of an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasConcludedLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact is concluded by the SPDX data creator to be governed by each `to` license.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 256, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).
Timestamp of impact statement.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: timeseries
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded in an ordered sequence of timestamped entries, such as the price of a stock over the course of a day.
Provides an IntegrityMethod with which the integrity of an Element can be asserted.
A value used in a CdxExtension name-value pair.
Provides a map of a property names to a values.
Records if sensitive personal information is used during model training or could be used during the inference.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeNotPresent
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The product is not affected because the code underlying the vulnerability is not present in the product.
Specifies the time an artifact was built.
Specifies the safety risk level.
